107.description: When setting up your cloud infrastructure, it's important to have a system in place so everyone involved is aware when changes occur and understands how to make those changes. In this talk, Dana will explain why an infrastructure-as-code system is the way to go for cloud infrastructure management, go over a few different options you have in the infrastructure management space (some of which are partially developed by her team at Google), and show you how to get started with Terraform, an open-source infrastructure-as-code tool
107.title: Infrastrcture Management on GCP

110.description: WebVR has come a long way since its inception in 2014. Multiple browsers are shipping with the API, and tools, frameworks and file formats have emerged to support a growing community of developers. The talk will start with a brief intro into our 2017 Mozilla tech road map and then discuss specifics of A-Frame.
110.title: Virtual Reality

111.description: Analytics is one of the four key pillars of Hootsuite product. In this talk Kiana Mohseni, Senior Director of Development at Hootsuite, will talk about the development process and technology stack behind Analytics product portfolio in Hootsuite.
111.title: Social Media Data Analytics

113.description: Voice driven interactions are becoming mainstream with technologies like Amazon’s Echo, Apple’s Siri, Microsoft’s Cortana, and Google’s Assistant. They are great for providing answers to common questions, getting local weather, playing music, and managing your lights. However, these technologies can do so much more. Let’s dive into how these technologies can be paired with more traditional web technologies to create interesting and unique experiences for our users.
113.title: Actions On Google with IoT and FireBase
